    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <head>407. Telegram 1372 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d407fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/12–1055. Confidential; Priority.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-12-10">December 10, 1955, 12:51 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d407-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d407-1"/>
                <p>1372. For <persName corresp="#p_ODL_1">David Osborn</persName>.</p>
                <p>Examine carefully entire record of talks and telegraph Department earliest
                    whether Chinese Communists ever told explicitly US would not negotiate subjects
                    involving rights and interests GRC without their presence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
